		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Infrared</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="metadata plainlinks topicon" id="protected-icon" style="position:absolute; z-index:100; right:55px; top:10px;">
<div><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#move" title="This article is move-protected due to vandalism."><img alt="Move protected" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Padlock-olive.svg/20px-Padlock-olive.svg.png" width="20" height="20" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Infrared_(disambiguation)" title="Infrared (disambiguation)">Infrared (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ir_girl.png" class="image" title="Image of two human bodies in mid-infrared (&quot;thermal&quot;) light (false-color)"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/cf/Ir_girl.png/250px-Ir_girl.png" width="250" height="166" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Ir_girl.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Image of two human bodies in mid-infrared ("thermal") light (<a href="/wiki/False-color" title="False-color">false-color</a>)</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Infrared</b> (<b>IR</b>) radiation is <a href="/wiki/Electromagnetic_radiation" title="Electromagnetic radiation">electromagnetic radiation</a> whose <a href="/wiki/Wavelength" title="Wavelength">wavelength</a> is longer than that of <a href="/wiki/Visible_light" title="Visible light" class="mw-redirect">visible light</a> (400-700&#160;nm), but shorter than that of <a href="/wiki/Terahertz_radiation" title="Terahertz radiation">terahertz radiation</a> (100&#160;µm - 1mm) and <a href="/wiki/Microwaves" title="Microwaves" class="mw-redirect">microwaves</a> (~30,000&#160;µm). Infrared radiation spans roughly three <a href="/wiki/Order_of_magnitude" title="Order of magnitude">orders of magnitude</a> (750&#160;nm and 100&#160;µm).</p>
<p>Direct sunlight has a luminous efficacy of about 93 <a href="/wiki/Lumen_(unit)" title="Lumen (unit)">lumens</a> per watt of radiant flux, which includes infrared (47% share of the spectrum), <a href="/wiki/Visible_light" title="Visible light" class="mw-redirect">visible</a> (46%), and <a href="/wiki/Ultra-violet" title="Ultra-violet" class="mw-redirect">ultra-violet</a> (only 6%) light. Bright sunlight provides <a href="/wiki/Luminance" title="Luminance">luminance</a> of approximately 100,000 <a href="/wiki/Candela" title="Candela">candela</a> per square meter at the Earth's surface.</p>
